The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 11: FMCG major Hindustan Unilever (HUL) today said its board had approved buying back shares worth Rs 630 crore from the market at a price of Rs 280 per share to utilise its surplus cash. HUL said the buyback price was at a premium of 20 per cent over the average closing price of the companys shares in the last three months.                            
	 New Delhi, June 11: Industrial production grew at a robust pace for the seventh consecutive month in April at 17.6 per cent, driven by capital goods and consumer durables. The rise in output was because of a strong performance by the manufacturing sector and a low base effect. Factory output had grown 1.1 per cent in April last year.                            
	 New Delhi, June 11: RIL has discovered oil in one of its exploration blocks in Gujarats Cambay basin. However, it did not give the reserves that the latest find may hold. This is its sixth oil discovery in the region.                             
	 New Delhi, June 11: The government has raised the income tax exemption limit on gratuity to Rs 10 lakh from Rs 3.5 lakh with effect from May 24.                            
	 Mumbai, June 11: Sebi today slashed the maximum investment limit to one-fifth for a single foreign institutional investor at Rs 2,000 crore. The existing ceiling for a single FII is Rs 10,000 crore.                                                                                                                          
